sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>(Workload Reconciler)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Admission Scheduler<br/>(Periodic Loop)
    participant Cache as In-Memory Cache<br/>(Quotas, Flavors, State)
    participant RemoteAPI as Remote K8s API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,RemoteAPI: Flow 1: Job Admission (Single Cluster)

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl create job<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Mutating webhook call<br/>Auth: API Server client cert
    Webhook->>Webhook: 3. Default queue-name label<br/>Set suspend=true
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Job (suspended)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validating webhook call<br/>Auth: API Server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation OK

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Watch Job events<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job created event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Scheduler->>Cache: 5. Periodic scheduling cycle<br/>Pull pending workloads
    Cache-->>Scheduler: Pending workloads + ClusterQueue state
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Assign ResourceFlavors<br/>Check quotas, priorities, fair sharing
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Update Workload status (Admitted)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Unsuspend Job<br/>Inject node affinity<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job pods start running

    Note over User,RemoteAPI: Flow 2: MultiKueue Workload Distribution

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Submit job to management cluster<br/>Auth: User credentials
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create local Workload CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Admit with MultiKueue AdmissionCheck<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Controller->>RemoteAPI: 2. Create remote Workload + Job<br/>Auth: kubeconfig credentials (Secret)
    Note over RemoteAPI: Remote Kueue admits<br/>and runs the job

    RemoteAPI-->>Controller: 3. Watch remote Workload status<br/>Auth: kubeconfig credentials
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Sync status back to local Workload<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,RemoteAPI: Flow 3: Provisioning Request

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Create ProvisioningRequest CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Note over K8sAPI: Cluster Autoscaler watches<br/>ProvisioningRequest
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: 2. ProvisioningRequest status update<br/>(nodes provisioned)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Update AdmissionCheck → Ready<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Complete admission<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
